Police Minister Bheki Cele's spent some time with station commanders in the Cape Town metropole. He visited the Nyanga, Fish Hoek and Wynberg police stations on Thursday. Minister, Bheki Cele, speaks more on this. Courtesy #DStv403 JOHANNESBURG - Police Minister Bheki Cele says he's disappointed by the court ruling against the Hawks in the Norma Mngoma case. The High Court in Pretoria found the Hawks acted unlawfully when arresting Mngoma. Judge Cassim Sardiwalla has ordered that all information removed from her devices be restored. READ: Norma Mngoma dishes the dirt on Malusi Gigaba Last year her estranged husband, former Home Affairs minister Malusi Gigaba, laid charges against her for allegedly damaging a Mercedes G wagon. She was then arrested by the Hawks